 Senior. Shakespeareâ€™s comic brilliance is wrapped in gender-confused, unrequited love. Aquila infuses As You Like It with their unique blend of fun and entertaining theatricality. ','',1,'Show','Loeb Playhouse','','2010-02-19 15:55:00','2010-02-22 16:00:00','2010-02-24 11:15:00','','\0','\0',1,0),(13,'AN ENEMY OF THE PEOPLE','With an all too familiar connection to the current events that cause us to question our business and civic leaders, Henrik Ibsen\'s gripping 1882 drama, An Enemy of the People, explores the impact of severe ecological issues on a small town, and one man\'s crusade to uncover the truth. When a trusted physician, Dr. Stockmann, makes the shocking discovery that the townâ€™s celebrated and profitable spa is toxic, tensions flare. The doctor must passionately defend his findings as he desperately tries to convince city hall of the life-threatening danger, placing his reputation, livelihood, and family at great risk merely because he is the bearer of the bad news. Originally set in a small town in Norway, but now placed in contemporary America, this classic is seen anew through the eyes of New Yorkâ€“based Aquila Theatre Companyâ€”described by The New York Times as â€œa classically trained, modernly hip troupe.â€ In their hands, Ibsenâ€™s timeless questions gain new resonance: When is it right to speak up? What would you risk for the truth?','',1,'Show','Loeb Playhouse','','2010-02-19 16:10:00','2010-02-22 16:00:00','2010-02-25 18:45:00','tsluis@purdue.edu','\0','\0',1,0),(14,'Martha Graham ','Founded in 1926 by dancer and choreographer Martha Graham, the Martha Graham Dance Company is the oldest and most celebrated contemporary dance company in America. With an extraordinary vision that forever altered the dance world, Graham created an expressive new aesthetic language that moved beyond the scope and structure of classical ballet. Graham drew inspiration from mythology, modern painting, and the American West, and collaborated with visual artists, fashion designers, and renowned composers. Her company was the training ground for many future modern choreographers, including Merce Cunningham, Paul Taylor, and Twyla Tharp, and virtually every major dance company today has been shaped by her influence. Grahamâ€™s extraordinary legacy is perpetuated today by the members of the Martha Graham Dance Company, who will bring several of her masterworks to Purdue -Errand into the Maze, Lamentation, and most notably the full production of Appalachian Spring, featuring music by Aaron Copland and the original set designed by sculptor and designer Isamu Noguchi. ','',1,'Show','Elliott Hall of Music','','2010-02-19 16:16:00','2010-02-24 16:00:00','2010-02-27 18:45:00','iboze@purdue.edu','\0','\0',1,0),(15,'The Hobbit','','',1,'Show','Loeb Playhouse','','2010-02-20 14:10:00','2010-02-20 14:10:00','2010-02-20 14:10:00','lotsofwitz@yahoo.com','\0','\0',1,0),(16,'Kid Cudi','KiD CuDi (Scott Mescudi) first gained major attention after the release of his debut mixtape A Kid Named Cudi. In 2009 Kid Cudiâ€™s single \"Day \'n\' Nite\" reached the top ten of the Billboard Hot 100 and Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs charts. \"Day \'n\' Nite\" is part of Cudi\'s debut album Man on the Moon: The End of Day featuring the song â€œPursuit of Happinessâ€ with MGMT. Kid Cudi was nominated for three 2010 Grammy Awards for his singles, \"Day \'n\' Nite\" and \"Make Her Say.\"\r\n\r\nKid Cudi has also worked with Lady Gaga, Kanye West and Common and he is featured in the new comedy series â€œHow to Make it in Americaâ€ on HBO.\r\n\r\nB.o.B. (Bobby Ray Simmons) is an American recording artist and producer from Atlanta, Georgia. His first single, \"I\'ll Be in the Sky\", was released in late 2008. About.com called the song a \"smart, funky artrap and a strong prelude to his album\" and included it at #13 on its subjective ranking \"Top 100 Rap Songs of 2008.\" B.o.B. currently has the #1 Heatseeker single on Billboard with â€œNothinâ€™ On Youâ€ (feat. 